{{Orphan|date=September 2016}}

In [[Roman mythology]], '''Vallonia''' was the goddess of valleys (cf. [[Latin]] ''[[Wiktionary: vallis|vallis]]'' "valley"). Her name is known from St. [[Augustine of Hippo|Augustine]]'s work ''The City of God'',<ref>[[Augustine of Hippo|Augustine]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=7Tp7iwzRyDMC&pg=PA145&dq=Forculus+roman+god&hl=en&ei=Ofa6TPS1EI7Nswa-gfnXDQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=book-thumbnail&resnum=1&ved=0CC8Q6wEwAA#v=snippet&q=The%20Romans%20could%20scarcely&f=false De civitate Dei, 4. 8]</ref> and is not attested otherwise.

